summary: This document contains correspondence, declarations, and memoranda related to the CIA's compliance with the JFK Assassination Records Collection Act of 1992. It includes letters from George Tenet, Director of Central Intelligence, to John R. Tunheim, Chair of the Assassination Records Review Board, declarations from Edmund Cohen and David W. Carey regarding the CIA's search and release of assassination-related records, and internal memoranda concerning the handling and replacement of declaration pages.
title: JFK Assassination Records Collection Act of 1992 Compliance Documents
